    • Constructor Detail

      • NeuralNetwork

        public NeuralNetwork(int[] layerSizes,
                     boolean zeroed)
        Parameters:
        layerSizes - - an integer array containing the number of neurons to be generated for each layer of the neural network. The first element in the array is the number of input neurons the neural network will have, the last element in the array is the number of output neurons, and any numbers in between correspond to the hidden layers of the neural network.
        zeroed - - if true , the weights of all of the neurons within the network will be automatically set to 0, and if false , the weights of the neurons with be generated randomly.

    • Method Detail

      • passInputs

        public void passInputs(double[] inputValues)
        Sets the activation values of the neurons of the first layer of the neural network. Note: this command DOES NOT tell the network to forward propagate. To tell the network to propagate these values, call the forwardPropagate() method of the network.
        Parameters:
        inputValues - - all values to be propagated forward by the network.
        See Also:
        forwardPropagate()

      • forwardPropagate

        public void forwardPropagate()
        Tells the network to produce outputs by propagating the input values given to it by the passInputs() method forward.
        See Also:
        passInputs(double[])

      • getOutputs

      • getRoundedOutputs

        public int[] getRoundedOutputs()

      • passCorrectOutputValues

        public void passCorrectOutputValues(double[] expectedValues)
        This function receives the values against which the neural network should compare its own outputs. These are the values used for calculating the cost and average cost of the neural network, as well as the target values used to calculate derivatives during backpropagation.
        Parameters:
        expectedValues - - an array containing of the correct values for all of the output neurons.

      • computeSquareCost

        public double computeSquareCost()
        Returns the value of the cost function of the network, which is computed as the sum of the squares of the differences between the predicted output values and the actual output values.
        Returns:
        A floating point number with a value within the allowed range for floating point numbers.

      • computeAverageSquareCost

        public double computeAverageSquareCost()

      • backPropagate

        public void backPropagate()
        Tells the network to adjust its weights and biases using the correct output value given to it by the passCorrectOutputValues method by calculating the derivative of the cost with respect to each weight and bias and subtracting the derivative, multiplied by the learning speed, from the current value of the weight or bias. This brings the output of the network closer to the desired output.
        See Also:
        passCorrectOutputValues(double[])

      • setMilliLearningSpeed

        public void setMilliLearningSpeed(double microLearningSpeed)
        This functions sets the learning speed of the neural network in micro-units.
        Parameters:
        microLearningSpeed - - The learning speed of the neural network in micro-units (for example, passing a 1 will produce a learning speed of 0.000001). This value is multiplied by the calculated derivatives to determine the necessary change in each value associated with the neural network.
